'''National Mobilization Law''' ({{zh|s={{linktext|lang=cmn-Hans|中华人民共和国国防动员法}}}}) was legislated in the [[National People's Congress]] (NPC) of the [[People's Republic of China]] on 26 February 2010. The law gives the NPC Standing Committee the power to put the national economy and civilians in China, including foreign assets, in war-time footing if "state sovereignty, unification, territorial integrity or security is threatened."<ref name=ntdt>{{cite web |url = http://english.ntdtv.com/ntdtv_en/ns_china/2010-03-02/657086180651.html |title = Chinese Regime Passes New Military Mobilization Law |publisher = [[New Tang Dynasty Television]] |date = March 2, 2010 |accessdate = Aug 4, 2010 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20100306180745/http://english.ntdtv.com/ntdtv_en/ns_china/2010-03-02/657086180651.html |archivedate = March 6, 2010 |df = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.peopledaily.com.cn/90001/90776/90785/6903965.html |title=China's top legislature closes session, adopts national defense mobilization law |publisher = [[People's Daily]] |date = Feb 27, 2010 |accessdate = Aug 4, 2010 }}</ref> The law went into effect on 1 July 2010.<ref name=ntdt/>
