{{Politics of Serbia}}
A '''referendum on adopting a new constitution before the elections''' was held in the [[Socialist Republic of Serbia]] on 2 July 1990.<ref name=DD>[http://www.sudd.ch/event.php?lang=en&id=rs011990 Serbien, Sozialistische Republik (Jugoslawien), 2. Juli 1990 : Erlass einer Verfassung vor Neuwahlen] Direct Democracy</ref> Following the approval of the proposal by 97.25% of voters, the [[National Assembly of Serbia|Serbian parliament]] promulgated a new constitution on 28 September.<ref name=DD/> [[Serbian general election, 1990|Elections]] were subsequently held on 9 December.<ref name=DD/>
